        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 7 at 2:26PM EDT by NWS Louisville KY</headline>
        <description>At 226 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles southwest of Danville, moving southeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Peytons Store, Chilton, Forkland, Ellisburg, and Butchertown.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
